File: Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula. JOHANNESBURG - Afriforum wants to know whether Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula will be prosecuted or not. The Civil Rights group says Mbalula should face corruption charges over money he allegedly received to repay debt. READ: Driver's licence backlog | AfriForum demands grace period extension They have written a letter to the National Director of Public Prosecutions Advocate Shamila Batohi. Afriforum says the matter has been dragging on for far too long.